independent_work.et:
Independent work (96 academic hours): 
- Watching video lectures, familiarizing oneself with guidelines, and self-control test after reading in Moodle (1 h);
- Independent assignment: a critical evaluation and written peer-review of the research article (10 h); 
- Conducting a systematic literature review for one's own master's thesis background framework and presenting the review to other course participants  (76 h);
- Creating an infographic to give an overview of the work done and presenting it in the final seminars to fellow students (about 7 hours).


