description.et:
Written assignment: CRITICAL EVALUATION OF A SCIENTIFIC ARTICLE.
Pass-fail evaluation:
- a written assignment is a critical analysis of a peer-reviewed article based on an internationally recognized guide to the type of research;
- the decisions made towards the article are logical and relevant, the criticism is adequate and justified;
- an assignment is made in accordance with the guideline and uploaded in Moodle on time.

LITERATURE REVIEW for the background of one's own research.
Pass-fail evaluation:
-	the work submitted is an analytical, critical, and logically systematized review of scientific sources on the phenomenon under study;
-	the work consists of the following sections: title, introduction, methodology, results (thematic subchapters), summary, references, and appendices;
-	the formulation of the title of the work (the topic of the planned research) meets the requirements and contains the required parts;
-	in the introduction of the work, the choice of the research topic and the actuality of the topic, and the importance of the research are briefly explained;
-	the methodology part includes: description of literature search strategy (search date(s), at least 2-3 databases, search words, limitations, etc.), criteria for selection of research material, and description of articles selection process and search results;
-	the description of the literature search and selection process is relevant, logical, and observable, and it expresses the author's criticality of the source;
-	the thematic subchapters that form part of the results include explanations of the key concepts of the work and justifications for the selection, a description of the theoretical starting points, and comparison and conclusions of previous research results;
-	the summary includes: a brief summary of the result of the analysis of the sources (which is known about the topic), the derived research problem (which is not known about the research topic), and the aim of the research derived from the problem (how the knowledge gap is filled, how the research problem will be solved);
-	the research problem is clearly defined and formulated;
-	the formulation of the research aim meets the requirements and it allows to solve the research problem;
-	at least 8 relevant and reliable scientific literature sources have been used in the work;
-	the different parts of the work are logically coherent and the text forms an integrated whole;
-	the total length of the work does not exceed 5 pages (without a title page, references list, and appendices) and the structure and format of the work are in line with relevant guidelines;
-	the appendices attached to the work are appropriate and contain data on all scientific articles evaluated and used for the literature review.
